WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.040
Hi everyone, my name is Barret Schloerke and I'm on the Shiny team at Posit.

00:00:08.040 --> 00:00:12.600
Shiny team just came out with a new release of Shiny, version 1.2.

00:00:12.600 --> 00:00:18.920
In this release, we've integrated Narwhals, which allows us to wrap your data frame and

00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:25.000
allow us to do computations on it without knowing specific knowledge of your data frame.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:29.820
This is great because Narwhals is improving by the hour, and it's really neat to see

00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:31.700
their progress so quickly.

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:37.540
Today, I'm going to show you a simple app, how we show some PyArrow data, and I'm going

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:41.900
to show you all the different types that I can currently display.

00:00:41.900 --> 00:00:44.860
So let's check out this PyArrow application.

00:00:44.860 --> 00:00:50.860
In a pretty format, it has 11 lines of code, but really, the magic all happens in these

00:00:50.860 --> 00:00:54.060
last three lines where we render a data frame.

00:00:54.060 --> 00:00:56.860
Let's run this app.

00:00:56.860 --> 00:01:03.700
Our data is coming from the great tables package with the SMP 500, and we're using PyArrow

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:06.940
table to import that pandas data set.

00:01:06.940 --> 00:01:11.860
Given this PyArrow data, we can just use it like normal, and it shows up in our app.

00:01:11.860 --> 00:01:13.339
That's pretty awesome.

00:01:13.339 --> 00:01:20.820
There's like roughly three, four lines of code involved for the user, and it works seamlessly.

00:01:20.820 --> 00:01:26.860
If we check out an app where we're looking at both pandas, polars, which was added in

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:33.980
Shiny 0.9, but PyArrow and Narwhals support was added now in 1.2.

00:01:33.980 --> 00:01:34.980
So let's run this app.

00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:40.980
It's a little bit longer because there's more options, but the same concept still exists.

00:01:40.980 --> 00:01:48.639
So the SMP 500 given pandas data set as your original data, we have polars, we have PyArrow,

00:01:48.639 --> 00:01:54.000
and if you happen to just return Narwhals itself, you can do that as well.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:59.639
There are new methods being displayed for your render data frame, and please check them

00:01:59.639 --> 00:02:00.639
out.

00:02:00.639 --> 00:02:04.360
To learn more about this, check out PyShiny website component gallery, which will be linked

00:02:04.360 --> 00:02:05.360
down below.

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:10.520
Also, check out Narwhals so that you can see the latest support and what they have for

00:02:10.520 --> 00:02:11.520
their eager data frames.

00:02:11.520 --> 00:02:11.520


00:02:18.639 --> 00:02:19.639
Thank you.

00:02:19.639 --> 00:02:19.639


